    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Oil Filter Bypass Valve</title>
        <figure id="f3350010258" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh13/H13028.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Filter bypass valve removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Filter bypass valve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hooked shaped tool (tool size shown not to scale)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil cooler housing</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove lube filter adapter for access to the filter bypass valve, which is pressed in the
                oil cooler housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil bypass valve (only if defective) by inserting a hook shaped tool (obtain locally)
                and depressing the check valve, while catching valve seat. As an alternative method, use a slide hammer
                threaded through valve.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
